name: Deborah Chelette-Wilson
what_you_do: Deborah Chelette-Wilson is a trauma counselor, life and parent coach, author, and speaker who helps people transform stress and trauma into triumph to consciously design an empowered life.
who_you_serve: Women who are frazzled by too many demands on their time and people seeking to heal from stress, trauma, and past experiences.
social_proof: MHR, NCC, LPC credentials; Texas Licensed Professional Counselor; National Certified Counselor; HeartMath Practitioner; Professional Coach with over twenty years practice; Texas Authors Award for Best Woman's Novel (2017) for 'Sanctuary Found'.
signature_programs: Sanctuary Found (novel, Country Pathways, 2017); 'Today Is The Time To Care For Your Beautiful Self' (free ebook); online courses (unnamed)
business_focus: Counseling, coaching, and education company focused on helping people heal from stress and trauma to live empowered lives.
service_provided: trauma counseling, life coaching, parent coaching, speaking, online courses, author/books
